ut direct reflection isn't allowed. I see other tests use MethodHandles, and I'm wondering if the coverage tool might track the exact method call stack. Another option is using Groovy's InvokerHelper for invoking static methods, although that still utilizes reflection. I'm curious if the call site is in a generated Java stub file instead of a class file, which adds complexity. Got to consider potential module opening issues with \"privateLookupIn.\"\n\n**Inspecting test reports**\n\nI see that the report indicates no new tests, which is interesting. I'm wondering if that means they might discard something due to a test failure. It might be worth checking `tests/src.../build/reports/tests/test` to see if there are any external run results from a previous attempt. I might be able to read through those without needing to run anything. This could provide valuable insights into what happened!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_031e604dab9e4707016a2864eeb14c81978eb6372e253e91f2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKGUJHgfs-7MeLF-1F6yF5fa4rlVXcAUw5LTE0Su2YzU2En3DHIyJG40_WIgUKonCfmrrkuE24NoiuO1-Abh9TKsUN0FV5uhljurc21T6Lw4VCQbxu2pY2PMzH1NVoIGcMOk05T4Ijxp9drkupPBoWY90IB2VX8a92BME__dPtU_ZsbH6-WD7Jj1-9tvwCtTPfPR08HQ161PWpLAQPdtCWO049VgExJPw1OwBETsG2mDjOF4E7GPAwxHWwR1XMhTm2Q0G3Xen_pKTTCc5609VhZmwCwlAsWW7lNyr_8_8eWnh9SEH3NZPkrD03WrSjHbI0mNkJDNIr1yUjFDCreuUGwgqz8z3k9a8JuQSi35stVZ5MwjSAtb3uxatqNGmDVe7jZ_MNsNga0wVjHEmGvto9Q52gQhmP_u1GtCTtJP10D6uSUzhwn1XZPktkfNKys8eV5YqdhbLbv7LYs4Evle_x1EEDcJJho8w2OzPaHaVCbZ_wSFDf-TdXbxEM3t5mmJA1I1sbFWa8oxNmqDGwfqHWunJvwYWAf1t4h1Rk-sxBRUtHvNVMzVaCLnf2F-HrApsjUoUcm7eY1DwADEv-Hs00rbrZBrocmbzeLtxknqgitm9N24tfJ9xEVoLfdmwHidNadMibh0ErJtZyCwb1KI27kcgj6XdR8OhuFgN4otsb5ZDtp2LmxqVrDxgi1I_sM-H7VgMJ07NJT66f5NSZwUeobGERwb5Mci9JjZv6pyjn7p-ql6Yz72spiPyqghnir1seSxyo9JQZMd9bTIOCrHmlbnnpga5JWrgO_tJWAuzGNZDgXDQqNlZ_ftVZQRznboLYWtjWGMjUbLT2ABRlb-zpAS6QzkDxW4YOa0C6_nJCsM775sqG0f-OiL6JzRrtbxnhO9YJvsOiE8mH4PhVACyeqi6Xe_tGsAr3LAQpuIdv75